KVM looks like the [[virtualization]] solution for me. I've read that its comparable to [[QEMU]] in concept, and since I've had some experience with that, it shouldn't be too much to learn about.

I'm interested in the virtualization features coming in [[linux kernel 2.6.26]].

### Initial Reaction ==
My initial reaction to KVM is that its awesome. Thanks to a basic bridging setup, I've been able to place virtual machines right on the host network. I'm hoping that this can be done with a few virtual machines. If not, I'll give [[VDE2]] another try.

